Todd asked about just getting the three bolts off for the impeller -
Todd, engine in yes?  Just put the bus in gear + E-brake to hold it,
watch the wind-up and undo the three bolts!  What's the torque spec
(Bentley not handy) - like 14-18 lbs/ft or somesuch?  YOU DO NOT NEED TO
REMOVE THE SINGLE CENTER IMPELLER HUB BOLT!!  Just undo the 3 and you're
good to go - wiggle off the impeller...  The center one gets a few more
lbs/ft on it, but it doesn't need to be touched in the instant matter.
Just keep yer gol-durned hands AWAY from the cherry-flavor loctite...
Out where we can see them, mister!

And Tom said (smartly):  "...I'm assuming the engine isn't in the car?
Then the best and easiest way is with a flywheel lock which is a < $10
item..."  'Zactly!  Out of the car - use the flywheel lock!

